{{Platform |Guid=3045-4 |Name=Game Boy Advance |Aliases=Game Boy Advance SP,Gameboy Advance,GBA,Game Boy Player,GBA SP,Game Boy micro,Atlantis,Oxygen |Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/0/1992/2121789-gba.png |Deck=The third platform in the Game Boy line, the Game Boy Advance was offered in a multitude of colors and had three hardware offerings, the sideways Game Boy Advance, the flip Game Boy Advance SP and the tiny Game Boy Advance Micro. |ShortName=GBA |ReleaseDateType=Full |ReleaseDate=2001-03-21 |InstallBase=81,510,000 |OnlineSupport=No |OriginalPrice=100.00 |Manufacturer=Companies/Nintendo }} <div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"2121789-gba.png","path":"0\/1992\/","mime":"image\/png","sizes":"square_mini,square_avatar,square_small,scale_small,square_tiny,square_medium,scale_medium,screen_medium,scale_large,scale_avatar,scale_tiny,scale_super,screen_kubrick","caption":"GBA Types"},"background":{"file":"239847-gba_skin_template.gif","path":"0\/6763\/","mime":"image\/gif","sizes":"square_tiny,square_medium,screen_kubrick_wide,scale_tiny,scale_super,scale_medium,square_small,scale_avatar,square_mini,square_avatar,scale_large,scale_small,screen_medium,screen_kubrick","caption":""}}' />
==Overview== https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/12/121177/1705634-810156_gba_logo_super.png The Game Boy Advance (originally codenamed "Atlantis") was originally launched in [[Locations/Japan|Japan]] on March 21, 2001 and then in [[Locations/North_America|North America]] on June 11. It is the third platform in the [[Platforms/Game_Boy|Game Boy]] hand-held line and like it's predecessors, the Game Boy Advance established itself as the leader in the portable market. The Game Boy Advance continued the [[Platforms/Game_Boy_Color|Game Boy Color]] trend of offering different colors and special branded limited editions. It also established the trend of a periodic hardware redesign (see below), which was carried on with the [[Platforms/Nintendo_DS|Nintendo DS]] and DS Lite. The Game Boy Advance series has had sales of over 81 million worldwide, approximately 43 million of which are Game Boy Advance SP units.
==Launch Titles==
